Company Overview of Walton Street Capital, L.L.C.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Walton Street Capital, L.L.C. is a real estate investment firm. The firm typically invests in single asset transactions, distressed debt, loan restructurings, complex ownership situations, illiquid assets, targeted development, and entity recapitalizations. It seeks to invest in the development and acquisition of office, hotel, retail, industrial, multi-family, for-sale residential, senior and student housing, and golf assets through both individual, portfolio and company-level transactions with a gross asset cost of approximately $9 billion. Within single asset transactions, the firm acquires real estate assets which have significant cash flow and residual value enhancement potential; targe...
Walton Street Capital, L.L.C. is a real estate investment firm. The firm typically invests in single asset transactions, distressed debt, loan restructurings, complex ownership situations, illiquid assets, targeted development, and entity recapitalizations. It seeks to invest in the development and acquisition of office, hotel, retail, industrial, multi-family, for-sale residential, senior and student housing, and golf assets through both individual, portfolio and company-level transactions with a gross asset cost of approximately $9 billion. Within single asset transactions, the firm acquires real estate assets which have significant cash flow and residual value enhancement potential; targets the acquisition of real estate assets at a discount to their replacement cost or below their current market value; and invests in larger United States transaction with $100 million and up in value. It also makes private equity platform investments in real estate operators and operating companies which require capital to expand and create an enterprise with significant asset base and opportunities for upside potential through consolidation of fragmented asset ownership base. The firm primarily invests in United States and can also invest in international ventures with a focus on Mexico, India, Brazil, and Europe. The firm invests between $10 million and $100 million. It seeks to exit its investments between three years and five years. Walton Street Capital, L.L.C. was founded in 1994 and is based in Chicago, Illinois with additional offices in Mexico, Mexico and India.
